    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v40-cohort",
      "strategy_id": "v40-cohort",
      "cohort_label": "v40",
      "hypothesis": "v40 cohort - defensive overlay sweep on the v25-bot-excl-climbing universe. All 5 mirrors share v25 base (TP=100/SL=30, entry@T+60, 5s poll, no trailing TP, filters: top5<=30 + dd>-25 + vel<200 + age>=60 + climbing_t30_t45=1). Each adds ONE defensive filter informed by loss-postmortem dominant_patterns: (1) acceleration_t30 > -8 cuts strongly-decelerating pre-entry tokens (bucket <-7.68 had 30% losers vs 20% baseline); (2) buy_pressure_whale_pct < 0.30 caps anchor-buyer dominance (live_micro postmortem flagged [0.35,0.51] at 46.7% losers); (3) top5_wallet_pct <= 20 tightens existing concentration filter; (4) vel in [5,100] excludes both grinder and frothy-fastrunner tails (55% losers had vel<5, 30% had vel>30); (5) acc + whale stacked compounds the 2 strongest signals. Goal: identify which defensive overlay improves drop_top3 robustness without crushing trade volume. Note: holder_count >= N was REJECTED as a filter candidate - getTokenLargestAccounts caps at 19 (step 1 in collector/holder-enrichment.ts), and the getProgramAccounts upgrade (step 2) is blocked by current RPC provider - so 100% of dataset has holder_count <= 19.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 0,
        "target_n": 80,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "cohort-level - see individual variants"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
